        <section id="subscriptions" class="mb-16">
             <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-center text-black mb-2">Understanding Red Hat OpenShift Subscriptions</h2>
             <p class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-lg text-center text-[#4f4f4f] mb-8">The right subscription depends on your chosen infrastructure and workload needs. OpenShift provides tailored models for maximum performance and flexibility.</p>
             <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
                 <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-xl shadow-lg flex flex-col">
                     <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-black mb-3">OCP (Core-Based)</h3>
                     <p class="text-[#4f4f4f] mb-4 flex-grow">Designed for virtualized infrastructure like AWS EC2. Licensing is calculated based on the number of virtual CPU cores used by worker nodes.</p>
                     <div class="mt-auto pt-4 border-t border-gray-200">
                         <span class="font-semibold text-[#8a8a8a]">Best for: Cloud Deployments</span>
                     </div>
                 </div>
                 <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-xl shadow-lg flex flex-col">
                     <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-black mb-3">OCP (Bare Metal)</h3>
                     <p class="text-[#4f4f4f] mb-4 flex-grow">Intended for direct installation on physical servers. This model provides optimal performance and is licensed per physical CPU socket or core.</p>
                     <div class="mt-auto pt-4 border-t border-gray-200">
                        <span class="font-semibold text-[#EE0000]">Best for: On-Premises Performance</span>
                     </div>
                 </div>
                 <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-xl shadow-lg flex flex-col">
                     <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-black mb-3">OpenShift Virtualization</h3>
                     <p class="text-[#4f4f4f] mb-4 flex-grow">An add-on for OCP on bare metal. It enables running traditional Virtual Machines (VMs), including Windows, alongside containers on the same cluster.</p>
                     <div class="mt-auto pt-4 border-t border-gray-200">
                        <span class="font-semibold text-[#EE0000]">Key Differentiator for On-Premises</span>
                     </div>
                 </div>
             </div>
        </section>
        
